Detailed Description

cvmx_pko_mem_iport_qos

Notes: Sets the QOS mask, per port. These QOS_MASK bits are logically and physically the same QOS_MASK bits in PKO_MEM_IPORT_PTRS. This CSR address allows the QOS_MASK bits to be written during PKO operation without affecting any other port state. The engine to which port PID is mapped is engine EID. Note that the port to engine mapping must be the same as was previously programmed via the PKO_MEM_IPORT_PTRS CSR. This CSR is a memory of 128 entries, and thus, the PKO_REG_READ_IDX CSR must be written before any CSR read operations to this address can be performed. The index to this CSR is an IPORT. A read of any entry that has not been previously written is illegal and will result in unpredictable CSR read data.
